24/01/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- One police officer was killed on Thursday (January 24th) and six others were injured in an anti-terror operation in the southeast city of Gaziantep. 
Two terrorists with suspected ties to al-Qaeda were killed in the operation and another 18 were arrested. 
The operation was carried out in three stages. 
Police say they seized large amounts of weapons and documents during raids on a number of apartments around the city. 
(Anadolu news agency, DPA, NTV, Reuters - 24/01/08)
